The F/F0 of the CDs@ZIFs was gradually enhanced with the concentration of S2- increase under the optimal conditions. The linear range for this effect was observed to be between 1 and 400 μM, with a calibration curve of F/F0 = 0.0009 [S2-] + 1.253. The results in Fig. 4
                        A show a strong linear relationship (R2 = 0.9986) and a LOD of 330 nM (3 σ/S). The repeatability of the method was evaluated with a RSD (n = 7) of 0.7%. In comparison to previously reported fluorescence or visual methods (Table 1
                        ), the developed method shows comparable performance.
